<task id="WKSP-043" project="spaarke-workspace-user-configuration-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build wizard Step 3: Arrange Sections and Name Workspace</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, fluent-ui, code-page</tags>
    <estimated-effort>8h</estimated-effort>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <dependencies>042</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    <role>Senior developer implementing workspace personalization</role>
    <goal>Build wizard Step 3 where users arrange selected sections into grid slots via drag-and-drop, name their workspace, and optionally set it as default.</goal>
    <context>
      Step 3 is the final wizard step before saving. It shows the chosen template's grid layout with
      the selected sections as draggable cards. Users drag section cards between slots to arrange their
      workspace. An unassigned section area holds sections not yet placed in a slot.

      The workspace name input is required for create/saveAs modes. A "Set as default" checkbox lets
      users mark this layout as their default workspace. Section cards display the section icon and label.

      Drag-and-drop is the primary interaction model (no keyboard alternative was requested by the owner).
      The grid visually reflects the chosen template structure from Step 1.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - MUST render the template grid layout matching the Step 1 selection
      - MUST implement drag-and-drop for moving section cards between grid slots
      - Each section card MUST show icon + label from the section catalog
      - MUST include an "unassigned sections" area for sections not yet placed in slots
      - Workspace name Input is REQUIRED (non-empty validation) for create and saveAs modes
      - "Set as default" Checkbox MUST be included
      - MUST use Fluent UI v9 components (Input, Checkbox, Card) per ADR-021
      - In edit mode, MUST pre-populate slot assignments and workspace name
      - "Save" button (final step) MUST be disabled if name is empty
      - Drag-and-drop only — no keyboard reordering alternative required
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/solutions/WorkspaceLayoutWizard/src/</file>
  </relevant-files>
  <steps>
    <step id="1">Create a DraggableSectionCard component that renders a section as a compact card (icon + label) with HTML5 drag-and-drop attributes (draggable, onDragStart with section ID in dataTransfer).</step>
    <step id="2">Create a GridSlot component representing a single slot in the template grid. Accepts onDrop, shows the assigned section card or an empty placeholder with dashed border. Implements onDragOver (preventDefault) and onDrop (extract section ID from dataTransfer).</step>
    <step id="3">Create the ArrangeStep component that renders the template grid using CSS grid matching the selected template's rows/columns. Place GridSlot components in each grid cell.</step>
    <step id="4">Add the unassigned sections area below the grid: renders DraggableSectionCards for sections not yet placed in any slot. Sections dragged from here to a slot move between areas.</step>
    <step id="5">Manage slot assignments in state: Map of slotIndex -> sectionId. Support drag from unassigned to slot, slot to slot (swap), and slot back to unassigned (drag to unassigned area).</step>
    <step id="6">Add workspace name Input (required, with validation) and "Set as default" Checkbox above the grid area.</step>
    <step id="7">Handle edit mode: pre-populate slot assignments from existing layout, pre-fill name, pre-set default checkbox state.</step>
    <step id="8">Wire "Save" as the final WizardDialog action: disabled if name is empty, passes complete wizard state (templateId, slotAssignments, name, isDefault) to parent save handler.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Grid layout visually matches the selected template structure with correct rows and columns</criterion>
    <criterion>Section cards can be dragged between grid slots and the unassigned area</criterion>
    <criterion>Workspace name input validates as required (non-empty) before save is enabled</criterion>
    <criterion>"Set as default" checkbox is functional and its value is included in save payload</criterion>
    <criterion>In edit mode, existing slot assignments, name, and default state are pre-populated</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
